{"article_id":"LA33nTYGLKr3eZsV","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"But any move toward compromise with Democrats on fiscal issues quickly comes under attack from conservatives as a surrender","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"and unsettles the rank and file .","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"It is a dynamic","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"that has haunted Speaker John A. Boehner throughout the 112th Congress ,","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"as he has repeatedly been caught between the imperative","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"to govern","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"and the need","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"to satisfy the restive right .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"Mr. Boehner , of Ohio , has drawn fire this week","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"for removing a handful of House Republicans","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"who have defied the leadership","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"from their preferred committee seats , a step","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"he took","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"to enforce party discipline .","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"Mr. Obama made clear on Tuesday in an interview with Bloomberg News","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"that he was not going to budge on raising tax rates on income over $ 250,000 .","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"\" We ' re going to have to see the rates on the top 2 percent go up , \"","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"Mr. Obama said in his first interview since his re-election ,","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"\" and we ' re not going to be able to get a deal","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"without it . \"","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"Allowing an extension only of the middle-class tax cuts is just one possibility ,","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"and Congress may never get to that point","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"if an agreement can be reached","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"or if another alternative can be found .","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"And it would be a bitter pill for Republicans to swallow","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"since they have repeatedly called for an extension of all the expiring tax cuts ,","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"any increases could harm the economy .","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"But Republicans also know","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"they have a problem :","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"many liberal Democrats are more than willing to return to the Clinton-era tax code , and to allow across-the-board spending cuts to take effect ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"which disproportionately affect the military ,","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"rather than compromise too much with Republicans after the strong Democratic showing in the elections .","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"\" It ' s a terrible position","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"because by default , Democrats get what they want , \"","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"said Representative James Lankford , Republican of Oklahoma ,","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"who admitted","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"his party is boxed in .","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"In the debt ceiling fight , the tables might turn .","depth":4},{"id":39,"text":"Many conservative Republicans say","depth":5},{"id":40,"text":"they are willing to let the nation default","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"if Congress refuses to cut spending .","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"If the tax rate fight is resolved by the time","depth":5},{"id":43,"text":"the debt limit increase is needed ,","depth":5},{"id":44,"text":"Democrats will find themselves without the leverage","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"they now have","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"with the expiration of the lower tax rates a certainty","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"unless Congress acts affirmatively .","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"Newsletter Sign Up","depth":4},{"id":49,"text":"Continue reading the main story","depth":4},{"id":50,"text":"Please verify","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"you 're not a robot","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"by clicking the box .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"Invalid email address .","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"Please re-enter .","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"You must select a newsletter","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"to subscribe to .","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"Sign Up","depth":5},{"id":58,"text":"You will receive emails","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"containing news content , updates and promotions from The New York Times .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"You may opt-out at any time .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"You agree to receive occasional updates and special offers for The New York Times 's products and services .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"Thank you for subscribing .","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"An error has occurred .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"Please try again later .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"View all New York Times newsletters .","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"That is why in his opening bid","depth":6},{"id":67,"text":"to end the fiscal standoff ,","depth":6},{"id":68,"text":"Mr. Obama proposed a permanent policy change","depth":6},{"id":69,"text":"to let the president raise the nation ' s borrowing limit on his own -","depth":6},{"id":70,"text":"and why Senator Mitch McConnell of Kentucky , the Republican leader , reportedly laughed out loud at the idea .","depth":4},{"id":71,"text":"Popular opinion seems to be running against the Republicans .","depth":5},{"id":72,"text":"Most Americans support higher taxes on the rich ,","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"and a poll by The Washington Post and the Pew Research Center","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"released Tuesday","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"found","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"that 53 percent say","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"Republicans in Congress would and should be blamed","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"if Washington fails to reach a deal before January .","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"Just 27 percent said","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"Mr. Obama would deserve more blame ,","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"while 12 percent say","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"both sides would share the blame equally .","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"Most Republicans do not want tax rates to rise on anyone ,","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"and such national polls have little sway over House members in districts","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"drawn to favor one party over the other .","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"In November , 204 Republicans","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"- 88 percent of the House Republican Conference -","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"won at least 55 percent of the vote ,","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"according to David Wasserman , a House analyst at The Cook Political Report .","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"Thirty-five of them won at least 70 percent .","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"Speaker Boehner took as much fire from conservatives as from Democrats","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"after proposing a deficit-reduction plan","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"that would raise $ 800 billion in tax revenue over 10 years .","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"Conservative advocacy groups and conservatives on Capitol Hill were united in their condemnation .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"\" One party proposes 800 billion in tax increases .","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"In an effort","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"to counter them","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"and continue to be the ' low tax , small government ' party ,","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"the other party ' s leadership proposes","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"...","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"wait for it ...","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"800 billion in tax increases , \"","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"huffed Senator Rand Paul , Republican of Kentucky , on his Facebook page .","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"Given the difficulty of compromise ,","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"a fallback may emerge as a top option .","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"Republican leaders could take up legislation","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"already passed by the Senate","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"to extend tax cuts on income under $ 250,000 ,","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"attach a deferral or cancellation of the automatic spending cuts ,","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"and give Mr. Obama nothing else ,","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"denying requests for increased infrastructure spending , help for homeowners to refinance their mortgages , and extensions of the payroll tax cut and unemployment insurance .","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"Then Republicans would demand deep concessions on spending and changes to Medicare and Social Security as a price","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"to raise the debt ceiling a few weeks later .","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"Republicans say","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"any such decision","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"to follow that course","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"is still a ways off .","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"There are significant problems with this possibility ,","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"starting with the estate tax .","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"The Senate tax bill was silent on the federal tax on inherited estates ,","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"which means","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"if the House passes that legislation at the last minute ,","depth":14},{"id":123,"text":"estate taxes would rise to Clinton-era levels ,","depth":15},{"id":124,"text":"with inheritances over $ 1 million taxed at 55 percent .","depth":15},{"id":125,"text":"Currently the value of estates over $ 5 million is taxed at 35 percent .","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"John Engler , a former Republican governor of Michigan","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"who is president of the influential Business Roundtable ,","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"told Bloomberg News on Tuesday","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"that Congress should raise the debt ceiling high enough","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"to take the limit off the table for five years .","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"But Republicans are not about to give up that cudgel .","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"\" Our ground is on spending ,","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"and the president intends to continue to spend more","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"than he has coming in , \"","depth":13},{"id":135,"text":"said Representative Austin Scott , Republican of Georgia .","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"\" For conservatives like me , we don ' t want to see any debt ceiling increase","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"without spending cuts","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"to match . \"","depth":12}],"relations":[{"parent":277,"left":186,"right":276,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":186,"left":176,"right":185,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":152,"right":175,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":140,"right":151,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":140,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":151,"left":145,"right":150,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":145,"left":2,"right":144,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":3,"right":143,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":143,"left":141,"right":142,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":141,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":8,"right":149,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":146,"right":148,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":146,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":11,"right":147,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":157,"right":174,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":153,"right":156,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":156,"left":154,"right":155,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":154,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"attribu